          <div>
            <div class="faq-q">I&rsquo;m a wirehouse advisor at Morgan Stanley with W-2 grid commission. How does qualifying work?</div>
            <div class="faq-a">Wirehouse W-2 base salary plus grid commission (typically 40-50% of gross production) plus production bonuses plus net new asset bonuses qualifies under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.1-01/general-income-information" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fannie Mae B3-3.1-01</a> as variable income with 24-month average. RSU stock awards from Morgan Stanley LTIP qualify additionally under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.1-09/other-sources-of-income" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B3-3.1-09</a> with continuing vesting. We provide HR compensation letter documenting the grid structure and multi-year production history.</div>
