            <div class="faq-a">RIA principal S-corp combining W-2 reasonable comp + K-1 distributions from AUM-based management fees (typically 0.75-1.25% of AUM) qualifies under <a href="https://selling-guide.fanniemae.com/sel/b3-3.4-02/analyzing-returns-partnership-or-s-corporation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">B3-3.4-02</a> with 2-year history. The AUM fee recurring revenue model produces stable income foundation. We document the S-corp 1120-S with K-1s, the RIA Form ADV showing AUM and fee structure, and the custodial relationship statements confirming AUM totals.</div>
